The paper deals with the problem of completing a knowledge base by predicting additional true relationships between entities. This involves using neural tensor networks and semantic word vectors to generalize and improve the model's performance. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval and database management, which could place it in cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases).
